            <section class="second" id="faq">
                <h1 id="h1">FAQs</h1>
                <h3 id="h3">What is Fostered Care?</h3>
                <p>
                  
                    
                    What is Fostered Care?
                    Fostered Care is a free platform that connects foster families with licensed respite providers. It helps foster families find qualified caregivers who can provide temporary care for children in need, giving them a well-deserved break. The platform streamlines the process by offering an easy-to-use interface where families can browse available providers and schedule care with peace of mind, knowing that all providers are verified and vetted for safety.
                    
                    </p>
                <h3 id="h3">Who can use Fostered Care?</h3>
                <p>Fostered Care is intended for two groups: foster families who need respite care and licensed respite providers who offer services. Foster families can use the platform to find qualified caregivers who are ready to step in and assist with temporary care. Licensed providers can sign up to offer their services and connect with families in need of care. To ensure security and reliability, both foster families and respite providers must be registered with the Department of Human Services before using the platform.</p>
                <h3 id="h3">How does Fostered Care ensure safety?</h3>
                <p>Safety is a top priority at Fostered Care. We implement multiple measures to protect both families and providers. These include:

                    1.Mandatory Registration: All users must register through the Department of Human Services to access the platform, ensuring that only approved users can participate.
                    2.Provider Verification: Every respite provider undergoes a thorough verification process, including background checks and credentials validation, to ensure they meet all necessary requirements.
                    3.Secure Messaging: Our in-app messaging system keeps your communication secure and confidential. Foster families and providers can discuss care details without compromising privacy.
                    4.Ongoing Monitoring: We continually monitor the platform to ensure that all interactions and activities adhere to safety standards.</p>
                <h3 id="h3">Is Fostered Care really free?</h3>
                <p>Yes, Fostered Care is entirely free to use. There are no hidden fees or charges for foster families or respite providers to access the platform. Families can browse, connect, and schedule care with licensed providers without paying any registration or subscription fees. The goal is to make it as easy and cost-effective as possible for families to find the support they need, while giving providers a way to share their expertise with those who need it most.</p>
                <h3 id="h3">How do I get started?</h3>
                <p>Download the app, create an account, and complete the
                    registration process. Once verified, families can browse
                    available providers, and providers can connect with families
                    seeking care.</p>
